        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Niraj Public School - Ameerpet"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Ravi kumar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-08-21",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "We don't like the management, no respect and no minimum ethics in Niraj.\n\nSchool fee and transportation fee parents should pay through app only.  Few months back I visited the school and asked the management, transport fee is not reflecting on school app, they said we are working on the app we will update to you.\n\nTwo days back(Friday) they called me, and they said that transportation fee due date is over, and I asked about app issue and after reinstalling it is working. The fee due is showing 87,400, as a middle-class person I need a few days' time to pay this amount. Today(Monday) transport bus did not come to my place and my kid waited for 20 minutes and came back home. I asked the management and they said we stopped the transportation due to pending fee. From tomorrow we will not allow her to school, if comes we will not provide the lunch. I requested them to pay the fee in 2 to 3 days. they did not agree.\n\nI did not get any message or call about the fee due dates. As a parent, what should I do, I felt so sad on this situation. no moral values and ethics, I am feeling shameful my kid is studying in this school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
